{"metadata":{"role":"symbol","roleHeading":"Case","title":"TLSClientConnectionPropertyName.validationFlags","symbolKind":"case","modules":[{"name":"GIO"}],"fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"case"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"validationFlags"}],"externalID":"s:3GIO31TLSClientConnectionPropertyNameO15validationFlagsyA2CmF"},"kind":"symbol","sections":[],"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"tokens":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"case"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"validationFlags","kind":"identifier"}],"languages":["swift"],"platforms":["macOS"]}]},{"content":[{"text":"Discussion","level":2,"anchor":"discussion","type":"heading"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"GLib guarantees that if certificate verification fails, at least one"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"flag will be set, but it does not guarantee that all possible flags"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"will be set. Accordingly, you may not safely decide to ignore any","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"particular type of error. For example, it would be incorrect to mask"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"code":"expired","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" if you want to allow expired certificates,","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"because this could potentially be the only error flag set even if","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"other problems exist with the certificate. Therefore, there is no"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"safe way to use this property. This is not a horrible problem,"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"though, because you should not be attempting to ignore validation","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"errors anyway. If you really must ignore TLS certificate errors,"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"connect to [TLSConnection](\/\/documentation\/gio\/tlsconnection\/onacceptcertificate(flags:handler:)."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"validation-flags is deprecated:"}],"type":"strong"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"Do not attempt to ignore validation errors.","type":"text"}]}],"kind":"content"}],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO","doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/TLSClientConnectionPropertyName"]]},"schemaVersion":{"patch":0,"minor":3,"major":0},"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/TLSClientConnectionPropertyName\/validationFlags","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/gio\/tlsclientconnectionpropertyname\/validationflags"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"What steps to perform when validating a certificate received from"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"a server. Server certificates that fail to validate in any of the","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"ways indicated here will be rejected unless the application","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"overrides the default via [TLSConnection](\/\/documentation\/gio\/tlsconnection\/onacceptcertificate(flags:handler:)."}],"references":{"doc://GIO/documentation/GIO":{"type":"topic","abstract":[],"identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO","title":"GIO","url":"\/documentation\/gio","role":"collection","kind":"symbol"},"doc://GIO/documentation/GIO/TLSClientConnectionPropertyName":{"kind":"symbol","role":"symbol","url":"\/documentation\/gio\/tlsclientconnectionpropertyname","navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"TLSClientConnectionPropertyName"}],"type":"topic","fragments":[{"text":"enum","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"TLSClientConnectionPropertyName","kind":"identifier"}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/TLSClientConnectionPropertyName","title":"TLSClientConnectionPropertyName","abstract":[]},"doc://GIO/documentation/GIO/TLSClientConnectionPropertyName/validationFlags":{"role":"symbol","title":"TLSClientConnectionPropertyName.validationFlags","abstract":[{"text":"What steps to perform when validating a certificate received from","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"a server. Server certificates that fail to validate in any of the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"ways indicated here will be rejected unless the application","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"overrides the default via [TLSConnection](\/\/documentation\/gio\/tlsconnection\/onacceptcertificate(flags:handler:)."}],"url":"\/documentation\/gio\/tlsclientconnectionpropertyname\/validationflags","type":"topic","kind":"symbol","identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/TLSClientConnectionPropertyName\/validationFlags","fragments":[{"text":"case","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"validationFlags","kind":"identifier"}]}}}